Description: The Flight into Egypt; the Virgin and the Christ Child on donkey, led by Joseph; small plate; posthumous fourth state with extensive reworking with mezzotint rocker. 1633 Etching, with light surface tone
Curator's comments: For an impression of the first state and comment see F,4.100. An impression of this print is recorded as being presented to the BM by Thomas Wilson in 1831 (see the printed 'List of additions made to the collections in the British Museum in the year 1831', p.121).
